<subSubSection pageId="142" pageNumber="743" type="distribution">
<caption inLine="true" pageId="142" pageNumber="743" startId="142.[695,867,299,328]" targetBox="[81,673,306,722]" targetPageId="142">
<paragraph blockId="142.[695,1287,299,724]" pageId="142" pageNumber="743">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[695,871,299,328]" pageId="142" pageNumber="743">Distribution.</emphasis>
Restricted to Rwenzori Mts, SW Uganda and neighboring DR Congo.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="142" pageNumber="743" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="142.[695,1287,299,724]" lastBlockId="142.[82,1288,729,1159]" pageId="142" pageNumber="743">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[696,953,374,408]" pageId="142" pageNumber="743">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
Head-body 150 mm, tail 93 mm, ear 25 mm, hindfoot 26-5 mm. No specific data are available for body weight. The Rwenzori Vlei Rat is relatively large and robust, with large blunt head, short tail, and shaggy fur. It is apparently somewhat smaller than the Ethiopian Vlei Rat (
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Heuglin" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[772,893,650,684]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Otomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="142" pageNumber="743" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="typus">O. typus</taxonomicName>
). Fur is dark tawny brown above and slightly paler below, somewhat darker and more woolly than the Ethiopian Vlei Rat. Tail is short (c.60% of head-body length). Lower incisors have two deep grooves. M, has four laminae, and M? consistently has six laminae, fewer than other species within the 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Heuglin" baseAuthorityYear="1877" box="[896,1000,808,842]" class="Mammalia" family="Muridae" genus="Otomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="142" pageNumber="743" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="typus">O. typus</taxonomicName>
species group.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[84,1129,848,882]" pageId="142" pageNumber="743" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="142.[82,1288,729,1159]" box="[84,1129,848,882]" pageId="142" pageNumber="743">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[84,194,848,882]" pageId="142" pageNumber="743">Habitat.</emphasis>
Moist alpine grasslands and swamps at elevations of 3300-4400 m.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
